1) Used for logging purpose
2) Need log4j.jar. Add it to the build path
3) Level object: OFF, DEBUG, INFO, ERROR, FATAL, WARN, ALL
4) Filter: Whether it should be logged or not.
5) Has configuration file: log4j.properties. Properties in key value format
6) Appender: where to write the logs
7) layout: how to display the logs
8) Use ${variablename} to use the value
9) Pattern layout %m%n: each message followed by newline


1) OFF: nothing logged into the file

ALL< Debug 1000 < INFO 2000 < Warn 3000 <Error 4000 < Fatal 5000 <OFF






